verse_part: and it shall come to pass,
vengeance shall be taken on him
And it shall come to pass,
and I will look upon it,
And I will make of thee
Therefore it shall come to pass,
then I will go to the right;
then I will go to the left.
and in the breadth of it;
to bring them on the way.
according to the cry of it,
and ye shall rise up early,
And I will make thee swear
And let it come to pass,
and it shall come to pass,
And I bowed down my head,
and he gave up the ghost
so that he could not see,
and it shall come to pass
that I might have sent thee away
I am not worthy of the least
as a prince hast thou power
and thou wast pleased with me.
and if men should overdrive them
and take up the fifth part
hath caused me to be fruitful
do ye look one upon another?
then let me bear the blame
And they bowed down their heads,
and when thou dost overtake them,
then I shall bear the blame
And it shall come to pass,
And it shall come to pass
and I will make of thee
and on the crown of the head
